      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MAJOR ICON NZ (4) chased a handy one when third last start at Penrith, beaten 3.5 metres. Draws a few spots wider but has winning claims in this line-up. CLASSIC ANGELINA (7) showed what she is capable of when she raced wide in the middle stages before working to the front and fighting strongly to score narrowly at Penrith last week. Has to contend with a wide draw but should be race fit third-up so can go right on with the job. STARTIN TO GOGH (9) came from this row to win at Menangle last month and was good from a very wide barrier there last time. Draws for a trail and could be dangerous if he gets he gaps. FOR ALWAYS ARDEN NZ (1) gets the ace draw and should be approaching peak fitness may be ready to show more.",
